						<summary>

						<p>This is also very much damaged. It seems to be dated in Śaka 1320 in the reign of the Vijayanagara king <hi rend="bold">Virūpāksha</hi> (?). It records an agreement among the temple authorities including the <hi rend="italic">kōyil-nāyakam</hi> Nāṟpatteṇṇāyira-Bhaṭṭa, and the <hi rend="italic">kaṇkāṇi</hi> Vēṭṭamaṅgalamuḍaiyār to follow certain arrangements with regard to the procession of the (subsidiary) deities in the temple on the days of festival. Mention is made of the entrance [Tirujñā]nasambandaṉ-tiruvāśal, a temple (or shrine) of Irumarabuntūya-Perumāḷ and one of Vikrama-Chōḷiśvaramuḍaiya-Nāyanār. Reference is made to (the time of) Sundara-Pāṇḍyadēva also.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
